My wife is an Amerasian, child of Vietnames woman and American soldier.  In her fifth grade, one of the kid said to her...your father killed my family.  &quot; My whole family was destroyed by your father's B-52&quot;  Much more worst  happened to her but I have to respect her privacy.  In Vietnam, she is a American.  In America, she is Vietnamese.  <br><br>
Unlike most of the stereo type about Amerasian that born out of wedlock or prostitution that portrayed by the Communist North and by the Hollywood movies.  Her mom was a teacher a the time.  Three Vietnamese rich man wanted to marry her but she happened to fell in love with an American soldier at the English school.  Anyway, my wife is a lucky Amerasian.  She managed to graduate from high school in Vietnam and then graduate from collge in America.  Most Amerasian that I know, can't even read in Vietnamese.  They are the real victims of the war.  I honnestly feel that the U.S. government, especially the Vietnam Vets. should have some kind of program to help these Amerasian that are now living in America.  They faced many obstables and barriers.  They should be treated as sons and daughters of American soldiers who gave their youth away for the call of this country not as some kind of lowly refugees.
